defunct_organizations.name: Allied Control Council
defunct_organizations.purpose: To govern Germany in the immediate aftermath of World War II.

defunct_organizations.name: Arab Cooperation Council
defunct_organizations.purpose: To strengthen economic ties and coordinate political positions among Arab countries.

defunct_organizations.name: Central Treaty Organization
defunct_organizations.purpose: To prevent Soviet Union expansion and promote regional security in the Middle East.

defunct_organizations.name: Comecon
defunct_organizations.members: Soviet Union, Eastern Bloc countries, and others
defunct_organizations.purpose: To facilitate and coordinate the economic development of communist countries.

defunct_organizations.name: Council of Ambassadors
defunct_organizations.purpose: To execute some of the provisions of the Treaty of Versailles post World War I.

defunct_organizations.name: Customs and Economic Union of Central Africa
defunct_organizations.purpose: To establish a common market and customs union among member states.

defunct_organizations.name: Delian League
defunct_organizations.members: Various Greek city-states led by Athens
defunct_organizations.purpose: To defend against Persian expansion and fund the defense of Athens.

defunct_organizations.name: Eurasian Economic Community
defunct_organizations.members: Belarus, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Russia, Tajikistan, and later Uzbekistan
defunct_organizations.purpose: To encourage economic integration among members; transformed into Eurasian Economic Union.

defunct_organizations.name: French Community
defunct_organizations.purpose: To maintain a degree of French influence in the post-colonial era.

defunct_organizations.name: French Union
defunct_organizations.members: France and its overseas territories and colonies
defunct_organizations.purpose: To replace the French colonial empire with a new political entity.

defunct_organizations.name: G33
defunct_organizations.purpose: To address issues related to agriculture, food security, and trade.

defunct_organizations.name: International Authority for the Ruhr
defunct_organizations.members: Allied countries post World War II
defunct_organizations.purpose: To control the production of coal and steel in the Ruhr Area in Germany.

defunct_organizations.name: International Trade Organization
defunct_organizations.members: Proposed for United Nations member states
defunct_organizations.purpose: Intended to regulate international trade but never fully established.

defunct_organizations.name: Latin League
defunct_organizations.duration: 7th century BC to early 4th century BC
defunct_organizations.members: Latin tribes and cities in ancient Italy
defunct_organizations.purpose: To defend against external threats and resolve internal conflicts.

defunct_organizations.name: Latin Union
defunct_organizations.purpose: To promote and protect Latin culture and languages.

defunct_organizations.name: League of Corinth
defunct_organizations.purpose: To facilitate a unified Greek military action against Persia.

defunct_organizations.name: League of Nations
defunct_organizations.purpose: To maintain world peace and prevent future conflicts post World War I.

defunct_organizations.name: Peloponnesian League
defunct_organizations.duration: 6th century BC to mid-4th century BC
defunct_organizations.purpose: To provide mutual protection and maintain hegemony over the Peloponnese.

defunct_organizations.name: Organisation of African Unity
defunct_organizations.purpose: To promote unity and solidarity of African states; precursor to the African Union.

defunct_organizations.name: Southeast Asia Treaty Organization
defunct_organizations.purpose: To prevent communism in Southeast Asia.

defunct_organizations.name: Union of African States
defunct_organizations.purpose: To achieve greater political, economic, and social integration between African states.
